========================================================================
= tbclock v1.10                                                        =
========================================================================

tbclock is a fullscreen terminal clock that displays time in a binary
fashion or another. It features a few modules and games to play with
binary displayed time. By default the lines are horizontal and shows
hours, minutes and seconds, you can switch to a different behaviour
with -a, see man file.


Installation
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
./configure
make
make install


Notes
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
Thanks to Franck (Flux/Spir) @ irc.oftc.net for the original idea, to
Andrew Pantyukhin (sat at FreeBSD) for the FreeBSD port, Olivier Regnier
for bug report and ideas. And ... you ? Send questions and patches to
tamentis at neopulsar dot org ... thanks!


